For the salad, heat a griddle pan until hot. Rub the steak with olive oil and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cook on the griddle for 4-5 minutes on each side, or until cooked to your liking. Leave to rest.For the dressing, place all the dressing ingredients into a bowl, season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and mix well.To serve, place the kale onto a serving plate and top with the steak. Place the sweet potato and orange slices around the plate and drizzle over the dressing.